Shift while booting (Esc for v9 earlier version);
Highlight the normal booting item (which is highlighted by default);
&rsquo;e&rsquo; to edit;
Find the line starts with linux ....;
Delete &hellip; quiet splash $vt_handoff &hellip;,
Change ro (read only) to rw, and add init=/bin/bash to the end of the line;
Ctrl+x or F10 to boot using this modified temporary item;
Root shell will be available, passwd to modify and then reboot.

如果administrator之前没有密码, 可以F8进入安全模式, 再用命令行操作:
net user &lt;username&gt; /active:yes
net user &lt;username&gt; &lt;theNewPass&gt;

Many people have the problem of memorizing passwords in different web sites, so they decided to use one password for all the web sites. But the risk is obvious, if a hacker could get one of your accounts, it means all your accounts, maybe even your online bank.
Then one may try use different passwords for different sites &hellip; It becomes a vicious circle &hellip;
Here are some tips which you could use to generate your passwords.

